{"questionId":"22582","questionHtml":"<p>Solve the differential equation in part (a)(ii) to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> as a function of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>integrating factor (IF) is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mtext>t</mtext></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>D</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>t</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> The first constant must be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>, and the second can be any constant for the final&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em> to be awarded. Accept a change of constant applied at the end.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22582","referenceCode":"21N.3.AHL.TZ0.2a.iii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve the differential equation in part (a)(ii) to find x as a function of t.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}